"adj./adv.小心的(地)；谨慎的(地) 【英】 adj. adv.小心的(地); 谨慎的(地)(very carefully) adj. /adv. 小心谨慎的(地) = carefully = cautiously 【记】切ginger的时候要gingerly, 小心手! 吃炖肉的时候要gingerly因为ginger与肉很难分开! 【记】音:兢兢, 战战兢兢 gingerly (adv.)  1510s, ""elegantly, daintily,"" perhaps from Old French gensor, comp. of gent ""dainty, delicate,"" from Latin gentius ""(well)-born"" (see gentle). Meaning ""extremely cautiously"" is from c.1600."
